<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1273,1732]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1273,1300]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Arista apically with somewhat triangular, leaf-like expansion but neither dorsal nor ventral branches (“ 
<figureCitation box="[171,239,1309,1336]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,561,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1435,561,1877]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phortica (Ashima) watabei Sati &amp; Fartyal, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (frontal view); B, abdominal sternites; C, periphallic organs (caudal view); D, E, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in C–E; 0.5 mm in A, B." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884624/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[285,487,1309,1336]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="419 - 429" refId="ref34109" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J. &amp; Gao, J. J. (2005 b) The Phortica (s. str.) foliiseta species-complex (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from China and its adjacent countries. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30, 419 - 429." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[350,399,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2005b
</bibRefCitation>
); all postgonites nearly straight in ventral view; posterior postgonite apically pointed, as long as anterior ones; 2 anterior postgonites on one lateral lobe nearly parallel (“ 
<figureCitation box="[1080,1148,1345,1371]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1196,1400,1345,1372]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="419 - 429" refId="ref34109" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J. &amp; Gao, J. J. (2005 b) The Phortica (s. str.) foliiseta species-complex (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from China and its adjacent countries. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30, 419 - 429." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[1262,1312,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2005b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1273,1732]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,526,1381,1408]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Supplementary description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[965,1105,1381,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum">
<emphasis box="[965,982,1382,1407]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[999,1105,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 14–16. Cibarial, medial sensilla approximately 8 per side; posterior sensilla 6–7 per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1273,1732]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The antisymmetry is observed in the postgonites: in A-type, the left lateral lobe bears 2 anterior postgonites, and the right lobe 1 posterior and 1 anterior postgonites; but in B-type, 
<emphasis box="[902,1015,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vice versa</emphasis>
(“ 
<figureCitation box="[1041,1108,1489,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1887,1912]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,346,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[163,1424,345,1861]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 8. Phortica (Ashima) kerinciensis Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, posterior portion of scutum (dorsal view); C, medial and posterior sensilla on cibarium (dorsal view); D, fore tarsus; E, abdominal sternites; F, habitus (ventral view); G, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); H, aedeagus and postgonites; I–K, phallic organs (lateral, ventral and ventrolateral views, respectively; B-type). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C, D, G–K; 0.5 mm in B, E, F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884630/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1157,1361,1489,1516]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="419 - 429" refId="ref34109" refString="Chen, H. W., Toda, M. J. &amp; Gao, J. J. (2005 b) The Phortica (s. str.) foliiseta species-complex (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from China and its adjacent countries. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 30, 419 - 429." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[1223,1272,1489,1515]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2005b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
