<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1273,1732]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1634,1660]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[591,729,1633,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum">
<emphasis box="[591,608,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[623,729,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[860,950,1633,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliiseta">
<emphasis box="[860,950,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">foliiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, in having the abdominal sternite III wider than long (ch.22-1), widest among sternites (ch.23-1), and with dense setulae on medial surface (ch.26-1), but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
